    <div class="post" id="cantenaccio">
        <h3>Cantenaccio</h3>
        <p>
            In Italian, cantenaccio means 'door-bolt' which implies a highly organised and effective backline defense focused on nullifying opponents' attacks and preventing goal-scoring opportunities.
            Hence, the cantenaccio tactoc aims to rule out defeats as far as possible.
    
            It employs a very tight man-marking defense, with player staying deep in their own half to prevent any offense by the opponents by blocking any passage towards the goal.
        
            A 'libero' / sweeper is an additional defensive player which covers an opponent who manages to break the two lines of defense. 
            He is also tasked to control loose balls and double-mark an opponent when necessary. 
            And if the opposing team has a talented striker, the sweeper may be assigned to man-mark them. 
            With the libero providing an additional line of defense the other defenders and midfielders perform other assignments to prevent the opposition from scoring.

            The midfield and defensive back line keep the ball from getting near the goal, their primary objectives are to disrupt any offensive flow, put pressure on the attackers 
            and deny the opponent's best offensive players from getting the ball.
        </p>
